'''Tomazinho Futebol Clube''', commonly known as '''Tomazinho''', is a [[Brazil]]ian [[Association football|football]] club based in [[S<U+00E3>o Jo<U+00E3>o de Meriti]], [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro state]].

==History==
The club was founded on January 2, 1930,<ref name="Book">{{cite book|title=Escudos dos Times do Mundo Inteiro|publisher=Panda Books|author=Rodolfo Rodrigues|year=2009|page=73}}</ref> adopting similar colors and team kits as [[Club de Regatas Vasco da Gama]]. Tomazinho won the [[Campeonato Carioca (lower levels)|Campeonato Carioca Third Level]] in 1986, finish ahead of [[Esporte Clube Nova Cidade|Nova Cidade]].

==Achievements==

* '''[[Campeonato Carioca (lower levels)|Campeonato Carioca Third Level]]:'''
** '''Winners (1):''' 1986

==Stadium==
Tomazinho Futebol Clube play their home games at [[Est<U+00E1>dio Josias Jos<U+00E9> da Silva]], nicknamed ''Beronh<U+00E3>o''.<ref name="Book" /> The stadium has a maximum capacity of 3,000 people.<ref name="Book" />

